org.aludratest.config
Interface MutablePreferences

All Superinterfaces:
Preferences
All Known Implementing Classes:
SimplePreferences
public interface MutablePreferences
extends Preferences

Interface for configuration Preferences objects which can be modified. Instances of classes implementing this interface are passed to Configurable.fillDefaults(MutablePreferences) to create the default configuration before overwriting it with configuration from the various documented configuration locations.

Author:
falbrech

createChildNode

MutablePreferences createChildNode(String name)
Creates a child configuration node with the given name. If such a node already exists, it is returned.

Parameters:
name - Name of the configuration node.
Returns:
The newly created child configuration node, or the already existing child configuration node of the same name.

removeChildNode

void removeChildNode(String name)
Removes the child configuration node with the given name. If no such node exists, no action is performed.

Parameters:
name - Name of the configuration node to remove.

removeKey

void removeKey(String key)
Removes the configuration key-value pair with the given key from this configuration node. If no such key exists, no action is performed.

Parameters:
key - Key of the key-value pair to remove from this configuration node.
